          "treatment": "Symptom management: cholestyramine 4g PO TID for pruritus (may be poorly tolerated). Rifampicin 150-300mg PO BID (second-line for pruritus). Ursodeoxycholic acid (UDCA) 13-15mg/kg/day may shorten attack duration. Plasmapheresis for refractory cases. Nutritional support (fat-soluble vitamin supplementation: A, D, E, K). MCT oil for steatorrhea. Most attacks resolve spontaneously within weeks to months."
